    "There are three types of SR: backward elimination, forward selection, and bidirectional elimination.",
    "(c) Ridge regression: In situations when the independent variables are highly correlated, ridge regression is a technique for estimating the coefficients of multiple-regression models.",
    "It has been applied to a variety of disciplines, including engineering, chemistry, and econometrics.",
    "It is often referred to as Tikhonov regularization, after Andrey Tikhonov, and it is a technique for regularizing improperly posed issues.",
    "It is very helpful in reducing the multicollinearity issue in linear regression, which frequently arises in models with several parameters."
